cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO

The paper deals with the problem of multiview stereo reconstruction using deep learning, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also extensively uses convolutional neural networks (cs.LG) and incorporates traditional multiview stereo concepts (cs.GR) within a deep learning framework. Additionally, the paper involves context-aware cost aggregation and regression, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of reconstructing scene depth from images acquired by a camera, which is a topic that falls under robotics (cs.RO).
